summary: CSharpGL is a pure C# project that allows for modern OpenGL rendering in an Object-Oriented way. It meets common requirements in OpenGL rendering such as: modern rendering using GLSL shaders and vertex buffer objects; A winform control that wraps initialization of creating OpenGL context; structs support setting values for uniform variables in GLSL shader; OpenGL state switch wrappers; picking primitives in multiple vertex buffer objects; rendering text using build-in GLText object in 3D space world or UI(window space); a scene editor; different kinds of demonstrations to use CSharpGL.

Given attributes allow to forget about imperative way of step-by-step verification of validation conditions in many cases. This package contains 3 components: ExpressiveAnnotations.dll - core annotations assembly, ExpressiveAnnotations.MvcUnobtrusive.dll - MVC validators assembly and expressive.annotations.validate.js - unobtrusive validation script.

description: Description

A generic, concurrent, portable and flexible Object Pool for the .NET Framework, completely based on the Code Project article of Ofir Makmal (http://goo.gl/4qig6T).
Library is production ready and it is successfully working in real life systems.

Original source code has been modified, in order to introduce a Parameterized Object Pool, already drafted by Ofir Makmal in the comments of the article. 
Moreover, a few unit tests have been added, in order to improve code reliability, and a lot of other small changes have also been applied. 
Of course, all modified source code is freely available at the project URL of this package.

Many thanks to Ofir Makmal for his great work.
summary: A generic, concurrent, portable and flexible Object Pool for the .NET Framework.
